question:
Consider the following code snippet. What is the most likely state of `threadB` when the print statement executes?

```java
Thread threadB = new Thread(() -> {
    synchronized(someLock) {
        try { someLock.wait(); } 
        catch (InterruptedException e) {}
    }
});
threadB.start();
// Short delay to ensure threadB starts
Thread.sleep(100); 
System.out.println(threadB.getState());
```
